Author: TonyL#3577
Content:
@Alright https://dash.plot.ly/authentication dash have nice (it looks simple to use at least)auth module


At first install this dep: 
```pip3 install dash-auth==1.2.0
import dash_auth
```

Then add to code:
```
VALID_USERNAME_PASSWORD_PAIRS = [
    ['parsed_username_from_config_file', 'parsed_password_from_config_file']
]```
Then add before layout:
```auth = dash_auth.BasicAuth(
    app,
    VALID_USERNAME_PASSWORD_PAIRS
)```

Author: TonyL#3577
Content: So you can just create (pregenerate with pseudo RNG lets say) config.ini on your docker instances with app and share username/password to users alongside with IP

Author: TonyL#3577
Content: OAuth they have as well, so possible to create some permissioned accounts

Author: TonyL#3577
Content: It might be interesting: for example you can give one user permissions to check trades history only, other is your portfolio manager so you can give him permissions to open positions and etc
